  "description": [
    "THE EUREKA SENTINEL ESTABLISHED 1870 EUREKA NEVADA MARCH 25 1911 PUBLISHED SATURDAYS The Revolution In Mexico By Frederic J Hank in In tko annals of LatinAmerican revolutions there never has been one abounding in more features at once peculiar and remark able than the one now being waged in Mexico In the first place it is a revolution without a programme Its leaders protest against existing conditions yet they have not offered a definite plan for remedying those conditions In the second place it is in nowise a united revolution There are half a dozen centers of activity yet in each case the grounds upon wl icli it is based are different and no leader has appeared upon the horizon who can unify these various enemies of existing conditions into one solid phalanx of op position to the government In the third place it is a revolution predoomed to military failure for neither the men nor the muni tions are coming forward in sufficient quantities to make it really formidable And yet in spite of all these things it is expected to prove a political success President Porlirio Diaz has decided to remedy the abuses against which it is a"
  ],
